FBIS4-58852 "drnes089_j_94033" FBIS-NES-94-089 Daily Report 8 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Al-Bid Letters Delivered to Arab Leaders Al-Bid Letters Delivered to Arab Leaders EA0805192794 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 8 May 94 EA0805192794 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] In a statement on Voice of the Arabs Radio today, Dr. 'Abd-al-Aziz al-Dali, member of the politburo of the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] and secretary of the YSP Central Committee, called for the need to stop the fighting first and then to separate the combatants. He stressed to Egyptian President Husni Mubarak that he was convinced of the importance of giving the Arab League and the Arab brothers latitude for finding a solution to the Yemeni crisis. It is worth mentioning that Brother Dr. al-Dali has delivered a number of letters from Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, the deputy chairman of the Presidential Council and secretary general of the YSP Central Committee, to his brother leaders of fraternal Arab states.
